  subhead="Your latest reel is a forty-second time-lapse of a complete bathroom renovation in a 1930s semi in Kidlington. The camera captures the strip-out — smashing the old tiles, ripping out the avocado bath, cutting away the corroded copper behind the bath panel. Then the first fix — new 15mm copper supplies soldered from the airing cupboard manifold, a boss strap connection to the soil stack for the new WC position, PEX underfloor heating loops clipped to insulation. Then the second fix — a freestanding Victoria + Albert Amiata bath with floor-mounted Crosswater MPRO taps, a frameless walk-in shower with recessed Grohe Grohtherm SmartControl, a wall-hung Duravit Starck 3 WC on a Geberit Duofix frame, and a wall-mounted vanity with LED mirror. The final frame reveals the completed room — herringbone porcelain floor tiles, warm UFH, chrome fixtures gleaming against matt white sanitaryware. Eleven thousand views. A homeowner in Witney DMs: 'Incredible work. Our bathroom is from the 1980s — pink suite, leaking shower, terrible pressure. Want a complete refit like yours — freestanding bath, walk-in shower, wall-hung WC. Our room is about 3 by 2 metres. We have a combi boiler so no cylinder — is that a problem for a freestanding bath? We are in Witney. Can you come and measure up?' You are soldering a riser. Without AI DMs, the Witney message waits. With it, the AI confirms that a combi boiler can serve a freestanding bath and asks about the mains flow rate. She confirms gas combi, good flow. Monday you call: Witney 1980s pink suite strip-out, freestanding bath, walk-in shower, wall-hung WC, combi boiler, 3×2m, flow rate query, full refit."
